# Vector Store Overview

## Stack
- Vector DB: FAISS `IndexFlatL2` (exact L2 search)
- Embeddings: SentenceTransformer `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`

## Retrieval Flow
PDF → text extraction (PyMuPDF/fitz) → section-aware chunking (~700 chars) → embeddings → FAISS index → top‑k search (k=3) → if best distance > 1.75 ⇒ “No reliable answer”.

## Storage Layout
- Per document: `storage/<document_id>/faiss_index.bin` and `chunks_metadata.json`
- Registry of uploads: `storage/registry.json`
- Only one index loaded in memory at a time (the latest or selected document).

## Runtime Behavior
- On startup, loads the most recent document/index.
- Switch active document via `/select-document` (UI or API).
- Single-process, in‑memory search; no external vector service.

## Why FAISS Here
- Lightweight, in‑process, zero external dependency.
- Fast for small/medium corpora like single resumes.
- Exact search (no ANN) keeps results predictable.

## Limits / Notes
- PDF-only ingestion; no authentication.
- Exact search only (no ANN); re-upload rebuilds the index.
- Persistence is local filesystem; ensure `storage/` is kept if you want history.

## Quick Usage
```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
```
- Upload PDF via UI (`/upload-ui`) or POST `/upload`.
- Ask questions via UI (`/ask-ui`) or POST `/ask`.
